              <h2 class="panel-title"><a href="http://electrum.org/tutorials.html#offline-mpk">Performing an Offline Transaction</a></h2>
            </center>
          </div>
          <div class="panel-body">
            <ul>
              <li>[Online PC] Go to the send tab and make a transaction. Instead of sending it, Electrum will detect a seedless wallet and query for a location to save the transaction. Select your USB-Key.</li>
              <li>[Offline PC] Go to Settings -> Import/Export -> "Load raw transaction". Select your transaction from the USB-Key. It will detect it's not signed and will prompt you to do so now. Fill in your password and sign the transaction. Save the new, signed, transaction to your USB-Key.</li>
              <li>[Online PC] Go to Settings -> Import/Export -> "Load raw transaction". Select the signed transaction and it will ask you if you want to broadcast it.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
